Whose national park ?
Humans cut down the <ENAMEX TYPE="DATE">million year - old</ENAMEX> cypress forests in <ENAMEX TYPE="DATE">less than a century</ENAMEX> , but the story of their destruction is not over .
Amazingly , the ban on logging natural forests has not protected <ENAMEX TYPE="LOC">Chilan</ENAMEX> , the only single - species forest of hinoki cypress surviving in the world today .
